<emphasis box="[151,324,297,323]" italics="true" pageId="198" pageNumber="199">R. combreticola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="198.[151,1437,153,395]" pageId="198" pageNumber="199">
Below are described the adult males of 6 further species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Signoret" authorityYear="1874" box="[863,948,333,359]" class="Insecta" family="Aclerdidae" genus="Aclerda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="198" pageNumber="199" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[863,948,333,359]" italics="true" pageId="198" pageNumber="199">Aclerda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In addition, a figure of 
<taxonomicName authority="Hodgson &amp; Millar" authorityName="Hodgson &amp; Millar. Macropterous" authorityYear="2002" class="Insecta" family="Aclerdidae" genus="Lecanaclerda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="198" pageNumber="199" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macropoda">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="198" pageNumber="199">Lecanaclerda macropoda</emphasis>
Hodgson &amp; Millar
</taxonomicName>
is included (
<figureCitation box="[577,659,369,395]" captionStart="FIGURE 84" captionStartId="216.[151,250,1945,1970]" captionTargetBox="[171,1420,189,1920]" captionTargetId="figure@216.[161,1426,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="216" captionText="FIGURE 84. Lecanaclerda macropoda Hodgson &amp; Millar. Macropterous male. (Aclerdidae. Aclerdinae). Where A=cranial apophysis, D=simple pore, K=apex of antennal capitate seta and R=dermal reticulations on ocular sclerite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3774346" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3774346/files/figure.png" pageId="198" pageNumber="199">Fig. 84</figureCitation>
). This is followed by a brief review of the Rhodesaclerdinae.
</paragraph>
