<subSubSection pageId="198" pageNumber="199" type="key">
<key pageId="198" pageNumber="199">
<keyStep pageId="198" pageNumber="199">
<paragraph blockId="198.[151,1436,546,656]" pageId="198" pageNumber="199">
<keyLead pageId="198" pageNumber="199">
1. Antennae 1 or 10 segmented. Sclerotised ridges absent from around dorsal simple eyes. Abdomen with hs setae only. Claws without a denticle … 
<taxonomicName box="[432,537,575,597]" pageId="198" pageNumber="199">Aclerdinae</taxonomicName>
Cockerell................................................................. 2
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="198.[151,1436,546,656]" pageId="198" pageNumber="199">
<keyLead pageId="198" pageNumber="199">- Antennae 7 or 8 segmented. Sclerotised ridges present around dorsal simple eyes. Abdomen with both hs and fs setae. Claws with a denticle … Rhodesaclerdinae Hodgson &amp; Millar....................................................... 4</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="198" pageNumber="199">
<paragraph blockId="198.[151,1436,692,773]" pageId="198" pageNumber="199">
<keyLead pageId="198" pageNumber="199">
2. Adult male apterous. Legs extremely reduced to 4 ring-like segments. Penial sheath very short, only slightly longer than broad.................................................................. 
<taxonomicName authority="McConnell" authorityName="McConnell" authorityYear="1954" box="[1089,1346,722,744]" class="Insecta" family="Aclerdidae" genus="Nipponaclerda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="198" pageNumber="199" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1089,1232,722,743]" italics="true" pageId="198" pageNumber="199">Nipponaclerda</emphasis>
McConnell
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1359,1429,721,744]" captionStart="FIGURE 85" captionStartId="218.[151,250,1068,1093]" captionTargetBox="[369,1219,185,1038]" captionTargetId="figure@218.[363,1223,181,1042]" captionTargetPageId="218" captionText="FIGURE 85. Nipponaclerda biwakoensis (Kuwana). Apterous male. (Aclerdidae, Aclerdina) (after McConnell, 1954). Where H=antenna, I=anterior leg, J=posterior spiracle, K=metathoracic leg, and L=ventral view of penial sheath." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3774348" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3774348/files/figure.png" pageId="198" pageNumber="199">Fig. 85</figureCitation>
)
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="198.[151,1436,692,773]" box="[151,1436,751,773]" pageId="198" pageNumber="199">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,751,773]" pageId="198" pageNumber="199">- Adult male alate. Legs normally developed with 5 long segments. Penial sheath several times longer than basal width..... 3</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="198" pageNumber="199">
<paragraph blockId="198.[151,1436,810,920]" pageId="198" pageNumber="199">
<keyLead pageId="198" pageNumber="199">
3. Caudal extension on abdominal segment VIII well developed. Pleural setae absent from abdominal segment VIII. Penial sheath not articulating with abdominal segment VIII.............................. 
<taxonomicName authority="Hodgson &amp; Millar" authorityName="Hodgson &amp; Millar" authorityYear="2002" box="[1032,1346,839,861]" class="Insecta" family="Aclerdidae" genus="Lecanaclerda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="198" pageNumber="199" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1032,1163,839,860]" italics="true" pageId="198" pageNumber="199">Lecanaclerda</emphasis>
Hodgson &amp; Millar
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1359,1429,839,861]" captionStart="FIGURE 84" captionStartId="216.[151,250,1945,1970]" captionTargetBox="[171,1420,189,1920]" captionTargetId="figure@216.[161,1426,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="216" captionText="FIGURE 84. Lecanaclerda macropoda Hodgson &amp; Millar. Macropterous male. (Aclerdidae. Aclerdinae). Where A=cranial apophysis, D=simple pore, K=apex of antennal capitate seta and R=dermal reticulations on ocular sclerite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3774346" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3774346/files/figure.png" pageId="198" pageNumber="199">Fig. 84</figureCitation>
)
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="198.[151,1436,810,920]" pageId="198" pageNumber="199">
<keyLead pageId="198" pageNumber="199">
- Caudal extension on abdominal segment VIII at most a gentle curve. Pleural setae present on abdominal segment VIII. Penial sheath clearly articulating with abdominal segment VIII.......................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="Signoret" authorityName="Signoret" authorityYear="1874" box="[1274,1436,898,920]" class="Insecta" family="Aclerdidae" genus="Aclerda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="198" pageNumber="199" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1274,1349,898,919]" italics="true" pageId="198" pageNumber="199">Aclerda</emphasis>
Signoret
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<paragraph blockId="198.[151,1436,956,1008]" pageId="198" pageNumber="199">
<keyStep pageId="198" pageNumber="199">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,956,978]" pageId="198" pageNumber="199">
4. Antennae 7 segmented. Lateropleurite broad. Membranous area on scutum quadrate.... 
<taxonomicName authority="McConnell" authorityName="McConnell" authorityYear="1954" box="[1089,1346,956,978]" class="Insecta" family="Aclerdidae" genus="Rhodesaclerda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="198" pageNumber="199" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1089,1232,956,977]" italics="true" pageId="198" pageNumber="199">Rhodesaclerda</emphasis>
McConnell
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1359,1429,956,978]" captionStart="FIGURE 86" captionStartId="219.[151,250,1846,1871]" captionTargetBox="[160,1423,191,1821]" captionTargetId="figure@219.[151,1436,181,1821]" captionTargetPageId="219" captionText="FIGURE 86. Rhodesaclerda insleyae Hodgson &amp; Millar. Macropterous male. (Aclerdidae, Rhodesaclerdinae).Where D=simple pore and R=dermal reticulations on ocular sclerite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3774350" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3774350/files/figure.png" pageId="198" pageNumber="199">Fig. 86</figureCitation>
)
</keyLead>
<keyLead box="[151,1436,986,1008]" pageId="198" pageNumber="199">
- Antennae 8 segmented. Lateropleurite narrow. Membranous area on scutum triangular... 
<taxonomicName authority="Hodgson &amp; Millar" authorityName="Hodgson &amp; Millar" authorityYear="2002" box="[1108,1436,986,1008]" class="Insecta" family="Aclerdidae" genus="Kwazulaclerda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="198" pageNumber="199" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1108,1252,986,1007]" italics="true" pageId="198" pageNumber="199">Kwazulaclerda</emphasis>
Hodgson &amp; Millar
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</keyStep>
</paragraph>
</key>
